<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="log" id="log">log</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntaxe :
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">log</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">double</span> n<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
La fonction <code>log()</code> renvoie le <a href="http://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logarithme_naturel" class="urlextern" title="http://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logarithme_naturel"  rel="nofollow">logarithme naturel</a>
(de base <code>e</code>) du nombre <code>n</code>. Si <code>n</code> est négatif, une
erreur de domaine se produit ; tandis que si <code>n</code> est nul,
une erreur de portée se produit.
</p>

<p>
Pour calculer le logarithme de <code>n</code> en une base quelconque <code>b</code>,
vous pouvez utiliser :
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="kw4">double</span> res <span class="sy1">=</span> <span class="kw3">log</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span>n<span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="sy2">/</span> <span class="kw3">log</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span>b<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
Le C++ fournit également les implémentations suivantes :

</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">float</span> <span class="kw3">log</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">float</span> n<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// identique à logf() en C99</span>
    <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">log</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> n<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// identique à logl() en C99</span></pre>
<p>
